about.summary: Python parser for the CommonMark Markdown spec

name: commonmark
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "CommonMark" %}
{% set version = "0.7.3" %}
{% set sha256 = "5f20ebd91614c8d339d4cded314894feb5d9a54c3b52c1ff9883794557149ea8" %}

package:
  name: {{ name | lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn:  {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt
  entry_points:
    - cmark = CommonMark.cmark:main

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools

  run:
    - python
    - future

test:
  imports:
    - CommonMark
    - CommonMark.render
    - CommonMark.tests

  commands:
    - cmark --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/rtfd/CommonMark-py
  license: BSD 3-Clause
  summary: 'Python parser for the CommonMark Markdown spec'
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ericmjl
    - dpryan79
